org.usfirst.frc2022.sensors

Class CherryAN8

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.usfirst.frc2022.sensors.CherryAN8
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PIDSource

    public class CherryAN8
extends Object
implements PIDSource
    Functions for interfacing with the Cherry AN8 Magnetic Position sensors. All functions are accessible using the CherryAN8 class

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      CherryAN8(int channel)
      Constructor for a Cherry AN8 Magnetic Position Sensor This constructor assumes the minimum voltage possible is .5 volts, and the max voltage possible is 4.5 volts If that is not the case then call setMinVoltage() and setMaxVoltage() to change those values This constructor also believes that the offset for the sensor is 0, if that is not the case then call the other constructor.
      CherryAN8(int channel, double offset, boolean offsetIsRadians)
      Constructor for a Cherry AN8 Magnetic Position Sensor This constructor assumes the minimum voltage possible is .5 volts, and the max voltage possible is 4.5 volts If that is not the case then call setMinVoltage() and setMaxVoltage() to change those values
      CherryAN8(int slot, int channel)
      Constructor for a Cherry AN8 Magnetic Position Sensor This constructor assumes the minimum voltage possible is .5 volts, and the max voltage possible is 4.5 volts If that is not the case then call setMinVoltage() and setMaxVoltage() to change those values This constructor also believes that the offset for the sensor is 0, if that is not the case then call the other constructor
      CherryAN8(int slot, int channel, double offset, boolean offsetIsRadians)
      Constructor for a Cherry AN8 Magnetic Position Sensor This constructor assumes the minimum voltage possible is .5 volts, and the max voltage possible is 4.5 volts If that is not the case then call setMinVoltage() and setMaxVoltage() to change those values

    • Constructor Detail

      • CherryAN8

        public CherryAN8(int channel)
        Constructor for a Cherry AN8 Magnetic Position Sensor This constructor assumes the minimum voltage possible is .5 volts, and the max voltage possible is 4.5 volts If that is not the case then call setMinVoltage() and setMaxVoltage() to change those values This constructor also believes that the offset for the sensor is 0, if that is not the case then call the other constructor.
        Parameters:
        channel - - The PWM channel on the default module where the sensor is connected

      • CherryAN8

        public CherryAN8(int channel,
         double offset,
         boolean offsetIsRadians)
        Constructor for a Cherry AN8 Magnetic Position Sensor This constructor assumes the minimum voltage possible is .5 volts, and the max voltage possible is 4.5 volts If that is not the case then call setMinVoltage() and setMaxVoltage() to change those values
        Parameters:
        channel - - The PWM channel on the default module where the sensor is connected
        offset - - The angle the sensor is off from 0, can be anywhere between PI and -PI if in Radians 180 and -180 if in degrees
        offsetIsRadians - - Boolean value saying if the offset parameter is in radians

      • CherryAN8

        public CherryAN8(int slot,
         int channel)
        Constructor for a Cherry AN8 Magnetic Position Sensor This constructor assumes the minimum voltage possible is .5 volts, and the max voltage possible is 4.5 volts If that is not the case then call setMinVoltage() and setMaxVoltage() to change those values This constructor also believes that the offset for the sensor is 0, if that is not the case then call the other constructor
        Parameters:
        slot - - The slot in the CRIO where the analog module is placed
        channel - - The PWM channel on the module where the sensor is connected

      • CherryAN8
